1
00:00:05,965 --> 00:00:07,800
ARCHER: SAY WHEN.

2
00:00:07,842 --> 00:00:09,802
T'POL: WHEN.

3
00:00:09,844 --> 00:00:11,804
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU DRANK WINE.

4
00:00:11,846 --> 00:00:13,263
T'POL: UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES,

5
00:00:13,305 --> 00:00:15,808
I'LL ALLOW MYSELF
A SMALL INDULGENCE.

6
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:17,852
TRIP: MAKE MINE
A LARGE INDULGENCE.

7
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:19,979
[ CHUCKLES ]

8
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:22,648
ARCHER:
TO OUR SCIENCE OFFICER.

9
00:00:22,690 --> 00:00:25,275
IT'S BEEN ONE YEAR
TO THE DAY

10
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:28,195
SINCE YOU OFFICIALLY
JOINED OUR CREW.

11
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:30,739
TRIP: HERE'S TO MANY MORE.

12
00:00:30,781 --> 00:00:32,324
T'POL: I APPRECIATE
THE SENTIMENT,

13
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:34,785
BUT I'M SIMPLY CARRYING OUT
MY ASSIGNMENT.

14
00:00:34,827 --> 00:00:36,411
ARCHER: THAT'S NO SMALL
ACCOMPLISHMENT,

15
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,497
CONSIDERING THE PREVIOUS RECORD

16
00:00:38,539 --> 00:00:42,543
FOR A VULCAN SERVING ON
A HUMAN SHIP WAS TWO WEEKS.

17
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:44,003
T'POL: 10 DAYS.

18
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:48,549
I'VE BEEN FILLING OUT
YOUR ANNUAL CREW EVALUATION --

19
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,884
JUST A FORMALITY.

20
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:51,385
I UNDERSTAND.

21
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:54,972
THE HIGH COMMAND HAS REQUESTED
MY EVALUATION OF YOU.

22
00:00:56,932 --> 00:00:58,559
JUST A FORMALITY.

23
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,519
THERE'S SOMETHING IN YOUR RECORD

24
00:01:00,561 --> 00:01:02,354
I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO ASK YOU ABOUT.

25
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:04,857
WHILE YOU WERE STATIONED
IN SAUSALITO,

26
00:01:04,899 --> 00:01:06,316
YOU TOOK A FIVE-DAY LEAVE.

27
00:01:06,358 --> 00:01:08,027
YES?

28
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:11,780
YOU WENT TO AN OLD MINING TOWN
IN PENNSYLVANIA -- CARBON CREEK?

29
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:15,534
SEEMS LIKE AN ODD PLACE
TO TAKE A VACATION.

30
00:01:15,576 --> 00:01:17,870
VULCANS DON'T TAKE VACATIONS.

31
00:01:17,912 --> 00:01:22,791
ARCHER: THEN, IF I MAY ASK,
WHY'D YOU GO THERE?

32
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:26,921
T'POL: IS THIS PART
OF MY EVALUATION?

33
00:01:26,962 --> 00:01:29,006
ARCHER: JUST CURIOUS.

34
00:01:29,048 --> 00:01:31,050
T'POL: IT WAS A PERSONAL MATTER.

35
00:01:33,052 --> 00:01:36,471
TRIP: YOU HAD A PERSONAL MATTER
IN CARBON CREEK, PENNSYLVANIA?

36
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:39,641
TRIP, IF SHE DOESN'T
WANT TO TELL US --

37
00:01:39,683 --> 00:01:41,268
SEEMS A LITTLE UNFAIR.

38
00:01:41,309 --> 00:01:42,853
WE TELL HER PLENTY OF STORIES.

39
00:01:42,895 --> 00:01:45,146
T'POL: YOU'D LIKE ME
TO TELL YOU A STORY?

40
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:46,815
IF IT'S A GOOD ONE.

41
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:51,946
I WENT TO CARBON CREEK BECAUSE
I WANTED TO VISIT THE SITE

42
00:01:51,987 --> 00:01:55,323
OF FIRST CONTACT
BETWEEN HUMANS AND VULCANS.

43
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:59,453
ARCHER: THEN YOU WERE ABOUT
3,000 KILOMETERS OFF.

44
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:01,121
THAT TOOK PLACE IN MONTANA.

45
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:02,664
ACTUALLY, IT DIDN'T.

46
00:02:02,706 --> 00:02:05,584
TRIP: EVERY SCHOOLKID KNOWS
THAT ZEFRAM COCHRANE

47
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:10,047
MET THE VULCANS IN BOZEMAN,
MONTANA, ON APRIL 5, 2063.

48
00:02:10,089 --> 00:02:12,549
I'VE BEEN THERE.
THERE'S A STATUE.

49
00:02:12,591 --> 00:02:15,719
T'POL: IN FACT, THE VULCANS
VISITED EARTH LONG BEFORE THEN.

50
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:18,221
MY SECOND FOREMOTHER
WAS ONE OF THEM.

51
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:20,099
YOUR WHO?

52
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:24,103
MY MOTHER'S MOTHER'S MOTHER.

53
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,568
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO HEAR THE STORY?

54
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:40,119
MAN: ♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

55
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:43,288
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

56
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:47,126
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

57
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:50,796
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

58
00:02:50,838 --> 00:02:55,174
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

59
00:02:55,216 --> 00:02:58,887
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

60
00:02:58,929 --> 00:03:02,850
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

61
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,727
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

62
00:03:05,769 --> 00:03:09,148
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

63
00:03:09,188 --> 00:03:10,649
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

64
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:14,277
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

65
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:19,158
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

66
00:03:19,198 --> 00:03:21,493
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

67
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:26,373
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

68
00:03:26,414 --> 00:03:29,168
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

69
00:03:29,208 --> 00:03:34,840
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

70
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:36,842
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

71
00:03:36,884 --> 00:03:39,178
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

72
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:42,639
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

73
00:03:42,681 --> 00:03:47,186
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

74
00:04:13,461 --> 00:04:15,630
I CAN'T COMPENSATE.

75
00:04:15,672 --> 00:04:19,218
THE RE-FUSION PRESSURE
IS STILL DROPPING.

76
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:22,303
IF OUR ORBIT DECAYS ANY FURTHER,
WE'LL BE DETECTED.

77
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:23,722
[ BEEPING ]

78
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:26,558
THEY HAD GONE TO EARTH
TO INVESTIGATE THE LAUNCH

79
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,310
OF ITS FIRST ARTIFICIAL
SATELLITE CALLED<i> SPUTNIK.</i>

80
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:30,645
DURING THEIR THIRD WEEK

81
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,940
OF GATHERING INFORMATION
ABOUT HUMANITY,

82
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,734
THEIR IMPULSE MANIFOLD
BEGAN TO MALFUNCTION.

83
00:04:35,776 --> 00:04:39,320
THEY HAD NO CHOICE BUT
TO ATTEMPT AN EMERGENCY LANDING.

84
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:42,532
TRY TO FIND AN ISOLATED AREA.

85
00:04:42,574 --> 00:04:45,202
SEND A DISTRESS CALL
TO THE HIGH COMMAND.

86
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,586
WOMAN: 100 KILOMETERS.

87
00:04:54,628 --> 00:04:56,296
DEPLOY THE STABILIZERS.

88
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:59,716
OUR LANDING VECTOR IS TOO STEEP.

89
00:05:05,388 --> 00:05:07,141
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

90
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:21,280
[ SPARKING, SIZZLING ]

91
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:27,077
[ COUGHING ]

92
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:42,467
MAN: ARE YOU HURT?

93
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:45,386
WOMAN: I DON'T THINK SO.

94
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:47,722
CAPTAIN.

95
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:55,772
MAN: WHAT ARE YOUR ORDERS?

96
00:05:58,108 --> 00:06:01,153
ARCHER: WHY DID THE VULCANS
KEEP THIS A SECRET?

97
00:06:01,195 --> 00:06:03,655
T'POL: THE INCIDENT
IS WELL-DOCUMENTED

98
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:06,325
AT THE SCIENCE DIRECTORATE
AND THE SPACE COUNCIL.

99
00:06:06,365 --> 00:06:07,366
TRIP: ON VULCAN?

100
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:08,535
T'POL: OF COURSE.

101
00:06:08,576 --> 00:06:10,871
TRIP: HANG ON.

102
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:15,167
T'MIR WAS
YOUR GREAT-GRANDMOTHER?

103
00:06:15,209 --> 00:06:17,836
I'D BE THE LAST PERSON
TO QUESTION YOUR MATH,

104
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:20,797
BUT AREN'T YOU MISSING
A FEW GENERATIONS?

105
00:06:20,839 --> 00:06:22,924
<i>SPUTNIK</i> WAS 200 YEARS AGO.

106
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:25,426
DON'T FORGET
HOW LONG VULCANS LIVE.

107
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,888
RIGHT.

108
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:30,098
JUST HOW OLD ARE YOU?

109
00:06:31,892 --> 00:06:35,354
IT'S GOT TO BE IN HER RECORD.

110
00:06:35,394 --> 00:06:38,982
TRIP, THAT'S
CLASSIFIED INFORMATION.

111
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:43,820
ARCHER: PLEASE. GO ON.

112
00:06:47,282 --> 00:06:50,409
THEIR SUBSPACE TRANSCEIVER
WAS DAMAGED IN THE CRASH.

113
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:53,705
THEY HAD NO WAY OF KNOWING
IF THEIR DISTRESS SIGNAL

114
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:55,374
HAD EVEN BEEN TRANSMITTED.

115
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:58,543
THEY'D USED UP THEIR EMERGENCY
RATIONS WITHIN A WEEK.

116
00:06:58,585 --> 00:07:00,962
AFTER FIVE DAYS WITHOUT FOOD,

117
00:07:01,004 --> 00:07:04,465
THEIR SITUATION
WAS GROWING DESPERATE.

118
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,176
[ BEEPING ]

119
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:19,731
TWO LIFE-FORMS.

120
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:38,417
FASCINATING.

121
00:07:41,086 --> 00:07:45,506
ONE OF THOSE CREATURES
COULD SUSTAIN US FOR SOME TIME.

122
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:48,427
ARE YOU SUGGESTING WE EAT IT?

123
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:52,806
IT'S LOGICAL TO TAKE
EXTREME MEASURES TO SURVIVE.

124
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:55,058
EVEN RESORTING TO SAVAGERY?

125
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,978
THAT MAY NOT BE NECESSARY.

126
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:00,021
OUR SCANS SHOWED A SETTLEMENT

127
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:02,774
APPROXIMATELY
SIX KILOMETERS AWAY.

128
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:03,984
IF WE ARE EXPOSED,

129
00:08:04,025 --> 00:08:06,778
WE COULD CONTAMINATE
THEIR CULTURE.

130
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,406
AND WHEN THEY FIND OUR BODIES
AFTER WE STARVE,

131
00:08:09,448 --> 00:08:11,658
WILL THAT CONTAMINATE
THEIR CULTURE?

132
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:13,618
BETTER TO LEAVE THEM
WITH A MYSTERY

133
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:15,120
THAN WITH THREE LIVING ALIENS.

134
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:17,831
WE SHOULD AT LEAST INVESTIGATE
THE POSSIBILITIES.

135
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,292
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

136
00:08:20,334 --> 00:08:23,003
I'M WILLING TO TAKE THE RISK.

137
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:27,548
MESTRAL.

138
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:29,509
REMAIN HERE.

139
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:52,282
HOW DO YOU SUGGEST
WE PROCEED?

140
00:08:52,324 --> 00:08:55,827
WE'LL NEED TO DISGUISE
OURSELVES.

141
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,503
WE'RE HERE TO FIND FOOD,
NOTHING ELSE.

142
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:10,091
WE'LL KEEP CONTACT WITH THE
HUMANS TO AN ABSOLUTE MINIMUM.

143
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:15,805
IF WE MUST INTERACT
WITH THEM, I WILL SPEAK.

144
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,227
WHAT IS IT?

145
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:26,024
I BELIEVE YOU HAVE
THAT GARMENT ON...BACKWARDS.

146
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:51,383
PRISONERS?

147
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:53,634
THEY DON'T APPEAR
TO BE RESTRAINED.

148
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:56,221
MORE LIKELY LABORERS.

149
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:58,598
IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE
THESE PEOPLE WERE CAPABLE

150
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:00,559
OF LAUNCHING
AN ARTIFICIAL SATELLITE.

151
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,395
RADIO ANNOUNCER:
<i>AND HE GETS THE SIGN.</i>

152
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:06,273
<i>AND HERE'S THE PITCH.</i>
<i>[BAT HITS BALL</i> ]

153
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:08,525
<i>DIXON HITS A SCORCHER</i>
<i>DOWN THE RIGHT-FIELD LINE.</i>

154
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:11,027
<i>THE FIRST BASEMAN MAKES</i>
<i>A STAB AT IT, BUT NO.</i>

155
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:13,321
<i>ELLIS IS CHARGING HARD</i>
<i>FROM RIGHT FIELD.</i>

156
00:10:13,363 --> 00:10:14,989
<i>HE SCOOPS IT UP AND FIRES.</i>

157
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:16,324
<i>IT'S GONNA BE CLOSE.</i>

158
00:10:16,366 --> 00:10:18,159
<i>THERE'S A COLLISION</i>
<i>AT THE PLATE,</i>

159
00:10:18,201 --> 00:10:21,329
<i>BUT WILCOX HANGS ON TO</i>
<i>THE BALL, AND THOMPSON IS OUT!</i>

160
00:10:21,371 --> 00:10:24,791
[ GROANING ]
<i>OH, MY, WHAT A PLAY.</i>

161
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:26,960
<i>AND THAT'S TWO OUT.</i>

162
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:28,878
SOME TYPE OF COMBAT,
NO DOUBT.

163
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:31,465
I BELIEVE IT MAY BE
AN ENTERTAINMENT.

164
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,221
[<i> COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING</i> ]

165
00:10:38,263 --> 00:10:41,766
MAN: ♪<i> GENTLY FALLS</i>
<i>THIS LONELY...</i> ♪

166
00:10:47,772 --> 00:10:49,690
A COMMUNAL GATHERING PLACE.

167
00:10:49,732 --> 00:10:53,612
DO THEY HAVE FOOD?

168
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,489
IT APPEARS SO.

169
00:10:58,741 --> 00:11:00,910
REMEMBER.

170
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:03,121
I WON'T SPEAK.

171
00:11:04,498 --> 00:11:11,463
MAN: ♪<i> I KNOW THE REASON</i>
<i>YOU MUST BE AWAY</i> ♪

172
00:11:11,505 --> 00:11:17,260
♪<i> BUT, OH,</i>
<i>HOW MY TEAR GENTLY FALLS</i> ♪

173
00:11:22,516 --> 00:11:27,646
♪<i> GENTLY FALLS</i>
<i>THE FLOWING SNOW</i> ♪

174
00:11:29,147 --> 00:11:34,944
♪<i> GENTLY FALLS</i>
<i>THIS BITTER TEAR</i> ♪

175
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:39,115
♪<i> THE SANDS OF WAR</i>
<i>ARE KEEPING YOU FROM ME</i> ♪

176
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:40,575
MAN: ♪<i> FOR ANOTHER YEAR</i> ♪
WOMAN: ANOTHER?

177
00:11:40,617 --> 00:11:41,951
MAN: NAH, I'LL SETTLE UP.

178
00:11:41,993 --> 00:11:43,203
WOMAN: ALL RIGHT.

179
00:11:43,244 --> 00:11:44,538
MAN: I'M NEXT.

180
00:11:44,579 --> 00:11:47,415
MAN: ♪<i> OH, HOW MY TEAR</i>
<i>GENTLY FALLS</i> ♪

181
00:11:47,457 --> 00:11:48,583
CURRENCY.

182
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:51,169
YES. THE PAPER APPEARS
TO HAVE VALUE.

183
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:53,588
MAN: ♪<i> OH, HOW MY TEAR</i>
<i>GENTLY FALLS</i> ♪

184
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,590
THANKS, BILLY.

185
00:11:55,632 --> 00:11:59,427
WOMAN: WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

186
00:11:59,469 --> 00:12:03,056
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING
THAT DOESN'T REQUIRE CURRENCY?

187
00:12:03,097 --> 00:12:04,849
YOU MEAN FREE?

188
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:09,896
MAN: ♪<i> BUT, OH,</i>
<i>HOW MY TEAR GENTLY FALLS</i> ♪

189
00:12:09,937 --> 00:12:12,691
MAN: WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO CARBON CREEK?

190
00:12:12,731 --> 00:12:14,693
MAN: ♪<i> I KNOW THE REASON</i> ♪

191
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:17,736
T'MIR: WE HAD AN ACCIDENT WITH
OUR VEHICLE OUTSIDE YOUR TOWN.

192
00:12:17,778 --> 00:12:20,114
WOMAN: ARE YOU OKAY?
T'MIR: WE'RE FINE.

193
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:22,242
MAN: ♪<i> OH, HOW MY TEAR</i>
<i>GENTLY FALLS</i> ♪

194
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:23,784
YOU FOLKS MARRIED?

195
00:12:23,826 --> 00:12:25,412
NO.

196
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:29,332
WE'RE...BUSINESS ASSOCIATES.

197
00:12:29,374 --> 00:12:31,292
THERE'S A GAS STATION
UP THE ROAD.

198
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:32,835
I'D BE HAPPY TO GIVE YOU A LIFT.

199
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:35,463
NO, THANK YOU.

200
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:37,340
SUIT YOURSELF.

201
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:41,720
ANYBODY UP FOR A GAME?

202
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:42,970
QUARTER A BALL?

203
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,264
BOY: I'LL PLAY.

204
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:46,433
MAN: YOU BETTER ASK YOUR MOTHER,
JACKIE.

205
00:12:50,895 --> 00:12:52,355
COME ON, MOM,
WE COULD USE THE MONEY.

206
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:54,857
GO ON UPSTAIRS
AND DO YOUR HOMEWORK.

207
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:57,485
WOMAN: I'LL BRING YOU UP
SOME DINNER.

208
00:13:02,073 --> 00:13:04,492
MESTRAL: I'M UP FOR A GAME.

209
00:13:04,534 --> 00:13:05,660
T'MIR: WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

210
00:13:05,702 --> 00:13:07,954
I TOLD YOU
NOT TO SPEAK TO ANYONE.

211
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:09,372
MESTRAL:
I CAN DEFEAT HIM.

212
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:11,165
T'MIR: YOU DON'T EVEN
KNOW THE RULES.

213
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:12,917
MESTRAL: IT'S SIMPLE.

214
00:13:16,963 --> 00:13:19,215
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T HAVE
ANY MONEY.

215
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:21,842
HE DOESN'T.

216
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:25,263
WELL, SORRY, PAL.

217
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:26,847
THERE'S NOTHING IN IT FOR ME.

218
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:30,851
IT'S TIME FOR US TO GO.

219
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:32,061
WAIT A MINUTE.

220
00:13:32,103 --> 00:13:33,980
WE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO WORK SOMETHING OUT.

221
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:36,608
IF YOU WIN, I'LL PAY UP.

222
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:41,028
IF I WIN, YOUR BUSINESS
ASSOCIATE HAS A DRINK WITH ME.

223
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,739
WE ACCEPT YOUR TERMS.

224
00:13:42,781 --> 00:13:44,449
WE DO NOT.

225
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,454
THE GAME IS BASED
ON SIMPLE GEOMETRY.

226
00:13:49,496 --> 00:13:51,498
IT WOULDN'T CHALLENGE
A VULCAN CHILD.

227
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:53,708
T'MIR: NO.
MESTRAL: WE NEED THEIR CURRENCY.

228
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:54,959
WHAT IF YOU LOSE?

229
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:59,088
I'LL HAVE TO...
SOCIALIZE WITH HIM.

230
00:14:04,594 --> 00:14:07,221
WOULD YOU RATHER DIE
OF STARVATION?

231
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:14,521
TOUGH BREAK.

232
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:17,751
THE NUMBER-8 BALL...

233
00:15:17,792 --> 00:15:19,919
IN THAT POCKET.

234
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,636
[ BELL JINGLING ]

235
00:15:28,678 --> 00:15:29,970
MAN: IT'S AN EXCELLENT PRODUCT,

236
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:32,599
AND IF YOU THINK ABOUT IT,
FINANCIALLY...

237
00:15:32,640 --> 00:15:34,975
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

238
00:15:35,017 --> 00:15:37,771
MESTRAL: CRYOGENICS.

239
00:15:37,812 --> 00:15:40,064
DO YOU SUPPOSE
THEY'VE EXPERIMENTED

240
00:15:40,106 --> 00:15:41,399
WITH PROTEIN REPLICATORS?

241
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:43,401
T'MIR: WHY DIDN'T YOU ASK
THE MERCHANT?

242
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,611
YOU SEEMED WILLING

243
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:47,071
TO ENGAGE EVERYONE ELSE
IN CONVERSATION.

244
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:52,993
I THINK THAT WINE'S
GONE TO YOUR HEAD.

245
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,579
WHAT ARE YOU IMPLYING?

246
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:58,541
TWO VULCANS STROLL INTO A BAR,

247
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,251
HUSTLE A FEW GAMES OF POOL,

248
00:16:00,293 --> 00:16:03,421
AND WALK OUT
WITH AN ARMLOAD OF TV DINNERS.

249
00:16:03,463 --> 00:16:05,840
IT SOUNDS LIKE AN OLD EPISODE
OF "THE TWILIGHT ZONE."

250
00:16:05,882 --> 00:16:07,258
[ LAUGHTER ]

251
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,218
IF YOU'RE NOT INTERESTED
IN HEARING THE REST --

252
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:10,553
ARCHER: HOLD ON, HOLD ON.

253
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:13,264
WE DIDN'T SAY
WE WEREN'T INTERESTED.

254
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:25,735
THEY REALIZED
THEY COULDN'T RELY ON GAMBLING,

255
00:16:25,777 --> 00:16:27,987
SO THEY TOOK WHATEVER
EMPLOYMENT THEY COULD FIND

256
00:16:28,028 --> 00:16:31,532
WHILE THEY WAITED FOR
A RESCUE VESSEL TO ARRIVE.

257
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:36,287
[ GRUNTING ]

258
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:53,638
T'POL: BUT AS THE WEEKS PASSED,
IT SEEMED LESS LIKELY

259
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:56,474
THAT THEIR DISTRESS CALL
HAD BEEN RECEIVED,

260
00:16:56,516 --> 00:17:01,646
AND IT BECAME MORE DIFFICULT
FOR THEM TO AVOID THE HUMANS.

261
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:03,272
TV ANNOUNCER:
<i>THE TEST OF A NUCLEAR DEVICE</i>

262
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:06,776
<i>IS DESIGNED FOR TACTICAL USE</i>
<i>IN PLACE OF ARTILLERY.</i>

263
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:09,988
<i>ZERO HOUR WAS JUST AFTER...</i>

264
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:12,991
WOMAN: NOTHING LIKE AN ATOMIC
TEST TO MAKE YOUR DAY.

265
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,701
MESTRAL:
DOESN'T IT CONCERN YOU?

266
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:17,787
THE BOMB?
IT SCARES THE HELL OUT OF ME.

267
00:17:17,829 --> 00:17:22,124
I'D HATE TO SEE HUMANITY
DESTROY ITSELF.

268
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,919
WOMAN: THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

269
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:26,337
BOY: WANT TO SHOOT SOME 8-BALL?

270
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:28,006
WOMAN: JACK.

271
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,842
I'VE GOT A GEOMETRY MIDTERM
NEXT WEEK. IT'S GOOD PRACTICE.

272
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:34,303
NICE TRY, BUT THERE'S BETTER
WAYS TO PREPARE FOR A MATH TEST.

273
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:37,515
ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN MATHEMATICS?

274
00:17:37,557 --> 00:17:39,517
JACK: OH, IT'S WHAT I WANT
TO STUDY AT COLLEGE.

275
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:41,101
MECHANICAL ENGINEERING.

276
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:42,562
IF I GET TO GO.

277
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:44,104
YOU WILL.

278
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:46,106
HE GOT A SCHOLARSHIP.

279
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,692
ONLY A PARTIAL ONE.

280
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:50,277
IT'S STILL A SCHOLARSHIP,
AND YOU WORKED HARD FOR IT.

281
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:52,030
EVERYBODY'S BEEN PITCHING IN

282
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:55,533
TO HELP PAY FOR HIS EXPENSES --
BOOKS, ROOM AND BOARD.

283
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:58,118
WOMAN: YOU CAN SHOOT ONE RACK,
AND THAT'S IT.

284
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,871
YOUR BREAK.

285
00:18:02,373 --> 00:18:05,835
[<i> DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS,</i>
<i>GUNSHOTS</i> ]

286
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:25,730
[ SIGHS ]

287
00:18:25,772 --> 00:18:28,024
MAN: THIS IS THE
THIRD TIME THIS WEEK

288
00:18:28,066 --> 00:18:31,110
I'VE HAD TO FIX
MRS. GARRETT'S SINK.

289
00:18:31,151 --> 00:18:33,696
MESTRAL: PERHAPS SHE ENJOYS
YOUR COMPANY.

290
00:18:33,738 --> 00:18:35,448
IT MIGHT BE TOLERABLE

291
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:38,367
IF HER SON DIDN'T INSIST
ON CALLING ME MOE.

292
00:18:38,409 --> 00:18:40,160
WHY DOES HE DO THAT?

293
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:44,832
THERE IS A COMIC ACTOR KNOWN
AS A STOOGE WITH THAT NAME.

294
00:18:44,874 --> 00:18:47,543
THE BOY BELIEVES
WE HAVE SIMILAR HAIR.

295
00:18:47,585 --> 00:18:50,129
THERE<i> IS</i> A RESEMBLANCE.

296
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:52,632
THIS IS INTOLERABLE.

297
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:55,217
I'M A WARP FIELD ENGINEER.

298
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:56,970
THEN PERHAPS YOU CAN HELP ME

299
00:18:57,011 --> 00:18:58,888
CONSTRUCT
A SUBSPACE TRANSCEIVER.

300
00:18:58,930 --> 00:19:01,265
I TOLD YOU, IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

301
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:06,395
IF WE REMAIN HERE, WE'LL DIE.

302
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,982
T'MIR: THIS WORLD'S ON THE BRINK
OF SELF-ANNIHILATION.

303
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:12,777
MESTRAL: I DON'T BELIEVE THAT.

304
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:17,156
BECAUSE YOUR FASCINATION WITH
THIS SPECIES IS BLINDING YOU.

305
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:21,744
YOU SIT FOR HOURS EACH DAY
IN FRONT OF THIS IDIOTIC DEVICE.

306
00:19:21,786 --> 00:19:24,163
I'M DOING RESEARCH.

307
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:27,166
PERHAPS IF YOU SPENT MORE TIME
OBSERVING HUMAN BEHAVIOR,

308
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:30,586
YOU MIGHT NOT HAVE SUCH
A PESSIMISTIC VIEW OF THEM.

309
00:19:30,628 --> 00:19:32,212
T'MIR: OPEN YOUR EYES.

310
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:33,547
THEY REVEL IN VIOLENCE.

311
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:35,883
THEY DEVOTE WHAT LITTLE
TECHNOLOGY THEY HAVE

312
00:19:35,925 --> 00:19:38,218
TO DEVISING WAYS
OF KILLING EACH OTHER.

313
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,138
SO DID WE CENTURIES AGO.

314
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:44,391
THEY JUST HAVEN'T REALIZED
THEIR POTENTIAL YET.

315
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:46,102
WHAT POTENTIAL?

316
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:52,066
THEY HAVE GREAT EMPATHY
AND COMPASSION.

317
00:19:52,108 --> 00:19:54,777
LOOK HOW WE'VE BEEN MADE
TO FEEL WELCOME.

318
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:59,907
[ TURNS OFF TELEVISION ]

319
00:19:59,949 --> 00:20:04,286
ONLY BECAUSE
THEY BELIEVE WE'RE HUMAN.

320
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:06,706
IF THEY DISCOVERED THE TRUTH,

321
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:10,126
DO YOU THINK THEY'D BE
SO COMPASSIONATE?

322
00:20:15,798 --> 00:20:17,257
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

323
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:20,011
TO THE SHIP.

324
00:20:20,053 --> 00:20:21,804
WHY?

325
00:20:21,846 --> 00:20:23,472
THIS ANTENNA IS INADEQUATE.

326
00:20:23,514 --> 00:20:25,683
I BELIEVE I CAN USE

327
00:20:25,725 --> 00:20:27,643
A WAVEFORM DISCRIMINATOR
TO ENHANCE IT.

328
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:29,770
IT'LL BE SAFER
TO GO AFTER DARK.

329
00:20:29,812 --> 00:20:32,314
YOU CAN'T RISK
BEING FOLLOWED.

330
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:33,816
I NEED TO GO NOW.

331
00:20:33,858 --> 00:20:37,111
"I LOVE LUCY" IS ON TONIGHT.

332
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:48,039
MAN: HOWDY.
MESTRAL: HELLO.

333
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:02,302
[ BRAKES SQUEAL ]

334
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:04,972
HI. YOU'RE RIGHT ON TIME.

335
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,752
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

336
00:21:37,337 --> 00:21:40,382
MESTRAL: IT WAS DIFFERENT THAN
SEEING IT ON TELEVISION,

337
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:44,428
MORE...INVIGORATING.

338
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:47,306
WOMAN: WELL, THERE'S
ANOTHER GAME NEXT WEEK
IF YOU'D LIKE TO GO.

339
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:49,142
OR WE COULD DO
SOMETHING ELSE.

340
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:50,601
TAKE IN A MOVIE?

341
00:21:50,643 --> 00:21:52,561
THAT WOULD BE ENJOYABLE.

342
00:21:52,603 --> 00:21:55,982
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

343
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:57,441
YES.

344
00:21:57,483 --> 00:21:59,777
WHAT ARE YOU HIDING
UNDER THAT CAP,

345
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:01,737
A POINTED HEAD?

346
00:22:01,779 --> 00:22:04,740
YOU'RE NOT FROM MARS, ARE YOU?

347
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:07,367
OH, I-I-I DIDN'T MEAN
TO MAKE FUN OF YOU.

348
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:11,371
I'M NOT OFFENDED.

349
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:13,373
MAY I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

350
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:15,375
PLEASE.

351
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:18,378
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR...MATE?

352
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:19,964
YOU MEAN MY HUSBAND?

353
00:22:20,006 --> 00:22:21,257
YES.

354
00:22:21,299 --> 00:22:23,342
HE LEFT A LONG TIME AGO.

355
00:22:23,383 --> 00:22:26,137
JACK USED TO GET LETTERS
FROM HIM EVERY NOW AND THEN.

356
00:22:26,179 --> 00:22:31,058
THE LAST WE HEARD,
HE'D MOVED TO PHOENIX.

357
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:33,393
I WAS HOPING HE WOULD
HELP WITH JACK'S COLLEGE,

358
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:35,021
BUT I GUESS
WE'RE ON OUR OWN.

359
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:36,772
I CAN UNDERSTAND
WHY HE WOULDN'T WANT

360
00:22:36,814 --> 00:22:39,233
TO HAVE ANYTHING TO DO
WITH ME, BUT...

361
00:22:42,195 --> 00:22:43,696
I'M SORRY.

362
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:46,782
I'M USUALLY BETTER AT KEEPING
A LID ON MY EMOTIONS.

363
00:22:46,824 --> 00:22:48,534
IT'S -- IT'S NOT ALWAYS EASY.

364
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:50,953
I KNOW.

365
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:58,044
WELL, UM...

366
00:22:58,085 --> 00:23:01,964
I'M DUE BACK AT THE PINE TREE.

367
00:23:02,006 --> 00:23:04,508
WILL I SEE YOU LATER?

368
00:23:21,859 --> 00:23:23,401
OH, I-I-I DIDN'T MEAN TO.

369
00:23:23,443 --> 00:23:26,280
I THOUGHT -- I THOUGHT --
OH, GOD.

370
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:28,448
PLEASE, I WAS SIMPLY SURPRISED.

371
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:31,660
IT WAS...VERY PLEASANT.

372
00:23:31,702 --> 00:23:33,371
PLEASANT?

373
00:23:33,411 --> 00:23:35,289
WASN'T THAT
AN APPROPRIATE RESPONSE?

374
00:23:35,331 --> 00:23:37,750
WELL, IT'S BEEN A WHILE
SINCE I KISSED A MAN,

375
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:39,293
BUT, STILL, I WAS HOPING

376
00:23:39,335 --> 00:23:41,670
IT'D BE A LITTLE BIT
MORE THAN PLEASANT.

377
00:23:41,712 --> 00:23:44,924
I DID SAY<i> VERY</i> PLEASANT.

378
00:23:44,965 --> 00:23:47,134
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

379
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:52,890
WE'VE GOT COMPANY.

380
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:01,065
[ SIGHS ] I SHOULD GO.

381
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:07,487
THANK YOU AGAIN.

382
00:24:21,543 --> 00:24:24,338
WAVEFORM DISCRIMINATOR?

383
00:24:24,380 --> 00:24:27,800
I WENT TO A BASEBALL GAME
IN DOYLESTOWN.

384
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:30,344
MORE RESEARCH?

385
00:24:30,386 --> 00:24:31,804
MAGGIE INVITED ME.

386
00:24:31,845 --> 00:24:33,264
I DIDN'T THINK IT
WOULD BE A PROBLEM.

387
00:24:33,306 --> 00:24:35,599
THEN WHY DID YOU LIE
ABOUT IT?

388
00:24:35,641 --> 00:24:40,271
BECAUSE I KNEW YOU
WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND.

389
00:24:40,313 --> 00:24:45,067
YOU WERE ENGAGING
IN INTIMATE ACTIVITY.

390
00:24:45,109 --> 00:24:48,279
I DIDN'T INITIATE IT.

391
00:24:50,488 --> 00:24:53,491
YOU'RE TO HAVE NO FURTHER
CONTACT WITH THAT WOMAN.

392
00:24:55,244 --> 00:24:57,495
YOU CAN'T MAKE THAT DECISION.

393
00:24:57,537 --> 00:24:59,665
I'M STILL IN COMMAND.

394
00:24:59,706 --> 00:25:01,541
COMMAND OF WHAT?

395
00:25:01,583 --> 00:25:04,253
OUR MISSION IS OVER.

396
00:25:04,295 --> 00:25:06,005
IT'S TIME TO ACCEPT THE FACT

397
00:25:06,046 --> 00:25:09,549
THAT WE MAY NEVER
LEAVE THIS WORLD.

398
00:25:45,543 --> 00:25:48,964
I WAS JUST GONNA PLAY SOME POOL.
I DIDN'T MEAN TO BOTHER YOU.

399
00:25:49,006 --> 00:25:51,842
UM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

400
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:55,304
I WAS ABOUT TO MEDITATE.

401
00:25:55,346 --> 00:25:56,930
REALLY?

402
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:59,475
ARE YOU JUST TRYING
TO CLEAR YOUR MIND

403
00:25:59,517 --> 00:26:02,019
OR...REACH A HIGHER
SPIRITUAL PLANE?

404
00:26:03,729 --> 00:26:05,981
I SPEND A LOT OF TIME
AT THE LIBRARY.

405
00:26:06,023 --> 00:26:08,192
STUDYING MEDITATION TECHNIQUES?

406
00:26:08,234 --> 00:26:09,485
UH, DIFFERENT THINGS.

407
00:26:09,527 --> 00:26:12,446
UH, MOSTLY ABOUT PLACES
I'D LIKE TO VISIT.

408
00:26:12,488 --> 00:26:13,906
UH, LIKE TIBET.

409
00:26:13,947 --> 00:26:15,949
THE -- THE BUDDHIST MONKS THERE
MEDITATE EVERY DAY.

410
00:26:15,991 --> 00:26:20,037
AND IN INDIA, THEY'VE GOT
THESE MYSTICS CALLED FAKIRS.

411
00:26:20,079 --> 00:26:22,331
SUPPOSEDLY THEY CAN ALMOST
STOP THEIR HEARTS

412
00:26:22,373 --> 00:26:23,874
JUST BY USING WILLPOWER.

413
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:25,125
YOU'D BE SURPRISED

414
00:26:25,167 --> 00:26:27,753
WHAT A DISCIPLINED MIND
CAN ACCOMPLISH.

415
00:26:27,794 --> 00:26:31,173
WHAT ELSE DO YOU STUDY
AT THIS LIBRARY?

416
00:26:31,215 --> 00:26:34,552
ASTRONOMY, UM, LITERATURE.

417
00:26:34,592 --> 00:26:38,222
SOMETIMES I'LL JUST PICK A BOOK
OFF THE SHELF AND START READING.

418
00:26:38,264 --> 00:26:40,766
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
WHAT DO YOU LIKE TO READ?

419
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:44,228
I HAVE AN INTEREST IN ASTRONOMY,
AS WELL.

420
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:45,563
OH, REALLY?

421
00:26:45,603 --> 00:26:48,732
DID YOU KNOW THAT, UH,
MINUTES AFTER DUSK,

422
00:26:48,774 --> 00:26:50,276
WHEN THE SUN IS JUST RIGHT,

423
00:26:50,317 --> 00:26:53,653
YOU CAN SEE<i> SPUTNIK</i>
<i>WITH THE NAKED EYE.</i>

424
00:26:53,695 --> 00:26:55,697
MAYBE TOMORROW I COULD SHOW YOU.

425
00:26:55,739 --> 00:26:57,741
I'VE SEEN IT ALREADY.

426
00:26:59,910 --> 00:27:02,037
IT'S AMAZING.

427
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:04,248
DON'T YOU THINK?

428
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:07,209
WELL, I'LL LET YOU GET BACK
TO YOUR MEDITATING.

429
00:27:07,251 --> 00:27:09,920
IT WAS NICE TALKING TO YOU.

430
00:27:09,962 --> 00:27:11,922
AND YOU.

431
00:27:26,103 --> 00:27:27,313
MAN: MESTRAL!

432
00:27:27,354 --> 00:27:28,772
MESTRAL: HELLO.

433
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:31,649
HEY! I GOT TICKETS TO
THE BALL GAME THIS WEEKEND.

434
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:32,818
IT'S A DOUBLE-HEADER.

435
00:27:32,859 --> 00:27:36,113
TIM'S GOING, GAVIN, JACK.
MAGGIE.

436
00:27:36,155 --> 00:27:38,365
I'M AFRAID I CAN'T.

437
00:27:38,407 --> 00:27:39,657
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU LATELY?

438
00:27:39,699 --> 00:27:41,118
MAGGIE SAYS YOU HAVEN'T EVEN --

439
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:43,120
[ EXPLOSION ]
UGH!

440
00:27:43,162 --> 00:27:44,455
MESTRAL:
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT, BILLY?

441
00:27:44,497 --> 00:27:46,123
BILLY: YEAH.

442
00:27:46,165 --> 00:27:49,251
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING,
ALARM BLARES ]

443
00:28:00,804 --> 00:28:02,264
T'MIR: WHY DO YOU
NEED US HERE?

444
00:28:02,306 --> 00:28:04,016
MESTRAL: I'M LOOKING
FOR A PARTICLE WEAPON.

445
00:28:04,057 --> 00:28:05,725
THE ARMORY CASE --
HELP ME FIND IT.

446
00:28:05,767 --> 00:28:07,561
MAN: WHY?

447
00:28:07,603 --> 00:28:09,146
MESTRAL: THERE'S BEEN
AN ACCIDENT IN THE MINE.

448
00:28:09,188 --> 00:28:11,231
AT LEAST 20 MEN ARE TRAPPED.

449
00:28:11,273 --> 00:28:13,900
IT COULD TAKE THE HUMANS DAYS
TO FREE THEM.

450
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:15,861
T'MIR: WE CAN'T INTERFERE.

451
00:28:15,902 --> 00:28:17,571
MESTRAL: THEY'LL DIE.

452
00:28:23,701 --> 00:28:28,248
YOU'D LET THEM SUFFOCATE...
EVEN IF WE COULD PREVENT IT.

453
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:30,250
MAN: WHAT IF THEY
SEE THE WEAPON?

454
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:32,378
WE'LL BE CERTAIN THEY DON'T.

455
00:28:32,419 --> 00:28:38,425
AT BEST, THESE HUMANS
ONLY LIVE TO BE 60 OR 70.

456
00:28:38,467 --> 00:28:39,843
IS IT WORTH THE RISK

457
00:28:39,885 --> 00:28:42,221
JUST TO EXTEND THEIR LIVES
A FEW MORE YEARS?

458
00:28:42,262 --> 00:28:44,931
MAN: WE CAN'T CONTAMINATE
THEIR CULTURE.

459
00:28:44,973 --> 00:28:48,519
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH CONTAMINATION.

460
00:28:50,229 --> 00:28:52,814
IT HAS TO DO WITH COMPASSION.

461
00:28:52,856 --> 00:28:57,444
COMPASSION...IS AN EMOTION.

462
00:28:57,486 --> 00:29:01,323
THEY'RE MY FRIENDS,
AND I'M GOING TO HELP THEM.

463
00:29:01,365 --> 00:29:03,742
DON'T TRY TO STOP ME.

464
00:29:13,252 --> 00:29:16,296
[ JACKHAMMERS POUNDING,
INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

465
00:29:42,864 --> 00:29:45,158
[ ALARM BLARES ]

466
00:29:47,869 --> 00:29:50,872
[ BEEPING ]

467
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:52,583
YES.

468
00:29:52,625 --> 00:29:56,670
T'MIR: PROCEED 22 METERS,
THEN TURN RIGHT AT THE JUNCTION.

469
00:29:56,712 --> 00:29:58,756
Mestral: Understood.

470
00:30:00,257 --> 00:30:02,384
T'Mir: In eight meters,
you'll find a narrow opening

471
00:30:02,426 --> 00:30:06,722
near the ground that leads
to an abandoned shaft.

472
00:30:06,764 --> 00:30:08,599
MAN: I THINK WE NEED MORE
GUYS DOWN THERE, THOUGH.

473
00:30:08,641 --> 00:30:09,975
MAN: IS THE RIDE
FREE UP THERE?

474
00:30:10,016 --> 00:30:11,435
MAN: YEAH.

475
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:33,915
[ COUGHING ]

476
00:30:42,633 --> 00:30:44,884
T'Mir: There's a stratum
of quartz on the wall

477
00:30:44,926 --> 00:30:46,094
opposite the opening.

478
00:30:46,136 --> 00:30:48,347
MESTRAL: I SEE IT.

479
00:30:48,388 --> 00:30:51,975
SET YOUR DISPERSAL RADIUS
TO SEVEN DEGREES.

480
00:30:58,774 --> 00:31:00,734
TWO MORE METERS.

481
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,918
HOW FAR?

482
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:21,296
APPROXIMATELY 30 METERS.

483
00:31:27,010 --> 00:31:29,929
MAN: HERE, OVER HERE.

484
00:31:29,971 --> 00:31:31,431
[ COUGHING ]

485
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,652
T'POL: AFTER RESCUING
THE 12 MINERS,

486
00:31:43,694 --> 00:31:46,697
MESTRAL BECAME
SOMETHING OF A HERO THAT DAY.

487
00:31:46,739 --> 00:31:49,324
ARCHER: DIDN'T PEOPLE WONDER
HOW HE GOT THEM OUT?

488
00:31:49,366 --> 00:31:50,659
T'POL: I'M SURE THEY DID,

489
00:31:50,701 --> 00:31:53,787
BUT NO ONE EVER DISCOVERED
THE TRUTH.

490
00:31:53,829 --> 00:31:55,372
THREE MONTHS PASSED,

491
00:31:55,414 --> 00:31:58,417
AND JUST AS THEY HAD
RESIGNED THEMSELVES TO THE FACT

492
00:31:58,458 --> 00:32:02,128
THAT, IN ALL LIKELIHOOD,
THEY WOULD NEVER LEAVE EARTH...

493
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:04,464
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPING ]

494
00:32:14,683 --> 00:32:16,769
T'MIR.

495
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:17,977
Man: This is Captain Tellus

496
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:19,813
of the Vulcan
survey vessel<i> D'Vahl.</i>

497
00:32:19,855 --> 00:32:23,316
I am responding
to your distress signal.

498
00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:25,569
T'MIR: WE THOUGHT
IT WASN'T TRANSMITTED.

499
00:32:25,611 --> 00:32:28,029
Tellus: Your signal was received
by a Tellarite freighter.

500
00:32:28,071 --> 00:32:31,909
It took them some time to
forward it to the High Command.

501
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,119
We're approaching
the system now.

502
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:36,121
Meet us at the crash site
in three days.

503
00:32:36,162 --> 00:32:38,081
UNDERSTOOD.

504
00:32:56,099 --> 00:32:58,811
I HEAR YOU'RE LEAVING?

505
00:33:00,019 --> 00:33:02,188
THAT'S CORRECT.

506
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:04,983
WHERE TO?

507
00:33:05,024 --> 00:33:07,820
HOME.

508
00:33:07,861 --> 00:33:11,030
UP NORTH.

509
00:33:14,493 --> 00:33:16,787
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

510
00:33:16,829 --> 00:33:18,204
YOU'RE ABOUT THE MOST
INTERESTING PEOPLE

511
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:19,957
I'VE MET IN THIS TOWN.

512
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:24,002
I'M SURE YOU'LL MEET A LOT OF
INTERESTING PEOPLE AT COLLEGE.

513
00:33:25,838 --> 00:33:27,046
I'M NOT GOING.

514
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:30,634
WHAT? WHY NOT?

515
00:33:30,676 --> 00:33:32,552
WE COULDN'T COME UP
WITH THE REST OF THE MONEY.

516
00:33:32,594 --> 00:33:36,055
THE DEADLINE
FOR THE TUITION'S FRIDAY, SO...

517
00:33:36,097 --> 00:33:37,557
WHAT WILL YOU DO?

518
00:33:37,599 --> 00:33:40,519
KEEP SAVING, I GUESS.

519
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,979
FIND A JOB.

520
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:44,815
JACK: MOM DOESN'T WANT ME
ANYWHERE NEAR THE MINE,

521
00:33:44,857 --> 00:33:46,984
BUT THAT'S WHERE THE WORK IS
AROUND HERE.

522
00:33:47,025 --> 00:33:49,736
CAN YOU TRY AGAIN NEXT YEAR
FOR THE SCHOLARSHIP?

523
00:33:49,778 --> 00:33:52,280
I'LL REAPPLY,
BUT THERE'S NO GUARANTEE.

524
00:33:52,322 --> 00:33:56,159
I'M SURE THEY WILL
OFFER IT TO YOU AGAIN.

525
00:33:57,828 --> 00:34:00,121
AND IF NOT,
THERE'S ALWAYS THE LIBRARY.

526
00:34:00,163 --> 00:34:02,916
STILL A LOT OF BOOKS
I HAVEN'T READ.

527
00:34:02,958 --> 00:34:06,003
GOOD LUCK UP NORTH.

528
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:10,007
CARBON CREEK'S NOT EXACTLY
A VACATION SPOT,

529
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:13,301
BUT I HOPE
YOU'LL COME VISIT US.

530
00:34:13,343 --> 00:34:15,387
PERHAPS.

531
00:34:25,355 --> 00:34:28,274
HE TOOK THOSE COLLEGE BOARDS.

532
00:34:28,316 --> 00:34:32,905
GOT THE HIGHEST SCORE
OF ANYBODY IN THE COUNTY.

533
00:34:32,946 --> 00:34:36,408
IT'S NOT FAIR.

534
00:34:36,449 --> 00:34:38,994
[ DOOR SHUTS ]

535
00:35:48,187 --> 00:35:50,732
SO...YOU'RE THE LADY

536
00:35:50,774 --> 00:35:53,777
WITH THE INVENTION THAT'S
GOING TO CHANGE THE WORLD.

537
00:35:57,948 --> 00:35:59,282
[ RIPPING ]

538
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:04,121
[ RIPPING ]

539
00:36:08,083 --> 00:36:09,751
[ RIPPING ]

540
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:14,547
[ RIPPING ]

541
00:36:14,589 --> 00:36:15,966
[ RIPPING ]

542
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:36,778
MORNING.

543
00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:46,038
JACK?!

544
00:36:46,079 --> 00:36:47,413
[ CHUCKLES ]

545
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:49,207
JACK?!

546
00:36:56,131 --> 00:36:58,424
T'MIR: DIDN'T YOU TERMINATE
YOUR EMPLOYMENT?

547
00:36:58,466 --> 00:37:00,093
MAN: YES.

548
00:37:00,135 --> 00:37:03,304
BUT I PROMISED MRS. GARRETT I'D
REPAIR THIS SUCTION DEVICE.

549
00:37:03,346 --> 00:37:06,058
MESTRAL: IT'S UNFORTUNATE THAT
YOU'LL BE LEAVING THESE PEOPLE

550
00:37:06,099 --> 00:37:09,644
WITHOUT EXPERIENCING
ONE THING THEY HAVE TO OFFER.

551
00:37:09,686 --> 00:37:13,857
SUCH AS...ALCOHOL...
FROZEN FISH STICKS...

552
00:37:13,899 --> 00:37:16,943
THE CONSTANT THREAT
OF NUCLEAR ANNIHILATION?

553
00:37:16,985 --> 00:37:19,278
THERE'S MUCH MORE TO THEM.

554
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:21,364
YOU JUST REFUSE TO SEE IT.

555
00:37:21,406 --> 00:37:23,200
I'VE SEEN ENOUGH.

556
00:37:23,241 --> 00:37:25,202
I HAVEN'T.

557
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,370
I PLAN TO STAY HERE.

558
00:37:28,955 --> 00:37:31,083
IF THIS IS
YOUR ATTEMPT AT HUMOR --

559
00:37:31,124 --> 00:37:32,625
THEY'RE ON THE VERGE

560
00:37:32,667 --> 00:37:35,712
OF COUNTLESS SOCIAL
AND TECHNOLOGICAL ADVANCEMENTS.

561
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:39,632
I HAVE THE UNIQUE OPPORTUNITY
TO STUDY AN EMERGING SPECIES.

562
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:43,261
MAN: THAT'S WHAT YOU'VE DONE,
MUCH CLOSER THAN WE ANTICIPATED.

563
00:37:43,302 --> 00:37:47,599
YOUR DUTY IS TO RETURN TO VULCAN
AND REPORT YOUR FINDINGS.

564
00:37:47,640 --> 00:37:50,393
THERE'S STILL MORE TO LEARN
ABOUT THESE PEOPLE.

565
00:37:50,435 --> 00:37:52,771
ALL OF THEM OR JUST ONE?

566
00:37:52,812 --> 00:37:54,106
[ SIGHS ]

567
00:37:54,147 --> 00:37:57,025
THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH MAGGIE.

568
00:37:57,067 --> 00:38:00,486
SHE HAS HELPED ME APPRECIATE
THEIR CULTURE,

569
00:38:00,528 --> 00:38:03,322
BUT I DON'T INTEND TO REMAIN
IN CARBON CREEK.

570
00:38:03,364 --> 00:38:04,699
WHERE WOULD YOU GO?

571
00:38:04,741 --> 00:38:07,285
TO ONE OF THEIR LARGER CITIES
AT FIRST.

572
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:10,956
AFTER THAT, I'M NOT CERTAIN.

573
00:38:10,997 --> 00:38:13,125
THERE'S SO MUCH TO SEE.

574
00:38:13,166 --> 00:38:16,419
THE HIGH COMMAND
WILL NEVER ALLOW IT.

575
00:38:16,461 --> 00:38:19,005
TELL HIM IT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

576
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:24,052
T'MIR?

577
00:38:24,094 --> 00:38:29,182
T'MIR: PERHAPS I CAN
ARRANGE FOR YOU TO BE
ON THE NEXT SURVEY SHIP.

578
00:38:29,224 --> 00:38:31,143
IN ANOTHER 20 YEARS,

579
00:38:31,184 --> 00:38:36,022
RUNNING MORE STATISTICAL SCANS
FROM HIGH ORBIT?

580
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:39,025
THAT'S NOT ENOUGH.

581
00:38:58,253 --> 00:38:59,462
TELLUS: WHERE IS YOUR CAPTAIN?

582
00:38:59,504 --> 00:39:01,089
HE WAS KILLED IN THE CRASH.

583
00:39:01,131 --> 00:39:03,549
TELLUS: THERE WERE FOUR VULCANS
ABOARD YOUR VESSEL.

584
00:39:03,591 --> 00:39:06,219
MESTRAL DIED
IN THE CRASH AS WELL.

585
00:39:06,261 --> 00:39:08,429
WE CREMATED THEIR REMAINS.

586
00:39:40,086 --> 00:39:43,298
TRIP: DO YOU REALIZE YOU'VE JUST
REWRITTEN OUR HISTORY BOOKS?

587
00:39:43,340 --> 00:39:45,258
T'POL: A FOOTNOTE, AT BEST.

588
00:39:45,300 --> 00:39:46,592
TRIP: FOOTNOTE?

589
00:39:46,634 --> 00:39:48,511
THIS IS LIKE FINDING OUT
NEIL ARMSTRONG

590
00:39:48,553 --> 00:39:51,389
WASN'T THE FIRST MAN
TO WALK ON THE MOON.

591
00:39:51,430 --> 00:39:52,932
PERHAPS HE WASN'T.

592
00:39:52,974 --> 00:39:55,227
OH.

593
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:59,064
HOW LONG DID THIS MESTRAL
STAY ON EARTH?

594
00:39:59,105 --> 00:40:01,816
THE REST OF HIS LIFE,
PRESUMABLY.

595
00:40:01,858 --> 00:40:05,611
AND THAT WOULD BE, WHAT,
ANOTHER 100, 150 YEARS?

596
00:40:05,653 --> 00:40:07,280
POSSIBLY LONGER.

597
00:40:07,322 --> 00:40:08,531
[ SCOFFS ]

598
00:40:08,573 --> 00:40:10,825
AN ALIEN IS LEFT
ON EARTH IN THE 1950s,

599
00:40:10,867 --> 00:40:13,828
LIVES THROUGH, WHAT,
30 PRESIDENTS,

600
00:40:13,870 --> 00:40:17,082
TRAVELS THE WORLD,
AND NO ONE NOTICES HIM?

601
00:40:17,123 --> 00:40:19,376
AND WHAT HAPPENED WHEN HE
FINALLY KICKED THE BUCKET?

602
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:23,838
DID THE UNDERTAKER JUST SHRUG
AND IGNORE HIS EARS?

603
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:26,465
T'POL: YOU ASKED ME
TO TELL YOU A STORY.

604
00:40:26,507 --> 00:40:27,466
[ CHUCKLES ]

605
00:40:27,508 --> 00:40:29,052
IT WAS A GOOD ONE.

606
00:40:29,094 --> 00:40:31,637
BUT DID IT REALLY HAPPEN?

607
00:40:31,679 --> 00:40:36,475
AS I SAID, YOU ASKED ME
TO TELL YOU A STORY.

608
00:40:38,895 --> 00:40:43,275
DAMN, CAPTAIN.
SHE PUT ONE OVER ON US.

609
00:40:43,316 --> 00:40:45,360
YOU DID GO TO CARBON CREEK.

610
00:40:45,402 --> 00:40:47,737
IF YOU CHECK MY RECORD,
YOU'LL NOTE

611
00:40:47,779 --> 00:40:50,448
THAT I ALSO VISITED
YELLOWSTONE PARK

612
00:40:50,489 --> 00:40:52,491
AND THE CARLSBAD CAVERNS.

613
00:40:52,533 --> 00:40:56,162
I'M A SCIENTIST.
THAT INCLUDES GEOLOGY.

614
00:40:58,581 --> 00:41:00,499
THANK YOU FOR THE MEAL.

615
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:02,168
ARCHER: UH. MY PLEASURE.

616
00:41:02,210 --> 00:41:06,214
YOU'VE CERTAINLY
KEPT US ENTERTAINED.

617
00:41:06,256 --> 00:41:08,507
GOOD NIGHT.

618
00:41:17,350 --> 00:41:19,394
[ SIGHS ]
